\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12530893 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 Do you think they liked their position in life or do you think they would have liked to have been something else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid655614 SF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 Well, I - I don't know really but I think he' always been used to a jolly life - this fellow you k
now. The other one was a very serious man - a very nice man he was.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12530893 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 And you stayed with them two years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid655614 SF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12530893 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 What did you do after that? Was it then you went to live with your sister? Why did you leave this parson?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid655614 SF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 Because he was moved to another part, you know, this fellow will only be here so long and then he'll be moved. They were moved.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12530893 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 Do you think you'd have stayed if they'd not moved?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid655614 SF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 Oh no, I wanted another job - makes old women of young women.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12530893 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 What do you mean - being in service?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid655614 SF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 Oh lord, I - you know, hauling about their kids for them all the time. Didn't do a break. Just for a bit but it got monotonous you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12530893 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 Did they treat you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6714541\charrsid12273066 well}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066  though as a person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid655614 SF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 They'd treat you as a maid you see. You found the distinction as you went on you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12530893 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 Did you like it as a whole working for them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid655614 SF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 
I liked the children you see - it was the children I was for. No, I - they'd just say good morning if they saw you on the corridor and that but - of course this fellow mix with anybody - I've never seen a parson like this fellow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12530893 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 But this one didn't?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid655614 SF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 Oh no. No, they just liked to keep to their own quarters you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12530893 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 You did tell me earlier that you left because you couldn't stand the discipline didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid655614 SF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 Yes. Yes, yes. No, I don't think them sort of things are - are cut out for you when you - well, of course I wasn't very old was I.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12530893 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 You were only thirteen when you went and fifteen when you left.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid655614 SF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 Yes, yes. Fifteen when I come out - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12530893 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 Where did you go after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid655614 SF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 Well, I think I went to live with my sister I think - in the fruit shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12530893 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 This was on Lower Broughton Road in the fruit business?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid655614 SF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12530893 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 And you used to just help her did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid655614 SF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 Her and him - yes - one of the assistants there was four of us all together but - I was relation you see, I was her sister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12530893 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 And you had to serve in the shop - that was your job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid655614 SF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12530893 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 What hours did you work in the shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid655614 SF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 Nine o
'clock in the morning 'til eight o'clock at night. Nine o'clock on a Friday - twelve o'clock on a Saturday. Nine o'clock 'til twelve on a Sunday morning. I was ....
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12530893 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 Did you have holidays - did you get paid when you weren't working or if you had a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid655614 SF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 Oh, I never got any holidays at that. And do you know, some weeks if he wasn't about the shop and I was going out like on me half day -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12530893 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 Which was your half day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid655614 SF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 Wednesday afternoon. And when I come into me tea I used to empty the win
dow for them in me tea time. Well, my boyfriend was gone home for his tea you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12530893 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 You told me you were paid five shillings a week - did you think it was a fair wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid655614 SF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 I didn't. And if I'd just forgotten - if he wasn't about and I didn't get me - me pay he'd try twist me out of it the next week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12530893 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 This was your brother-in-law?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid655614 SF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 My sister's husband - Charlie.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12530893 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 How did you get on with him as a whole though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid655614 SF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 Well, he was - he was very nice but he liked a little drop to drink.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12530893 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 And this spoilt it for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid655614 SF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 
Well, it did when like - he hadn't much time, he looked after his business but - when he was like, got a bit merry, I had to laugh you know. Her and I used to go to the pictures Monday night but it's after she'd washed and 
dried and ironed, no wonder she went a bit mental. And we'd go out you see, well then about Thursday night I'd mind the shop and they'd go to the Regent Pictures - Cross Lane, you know - that was a little night out I used to take over then you see while t
h
ey went. And - we went and had a drink one night when - when they come back you see she didn't drink - she'd come home and he'd go and have a drink. Well, I think he got one over the mark one night - so, when he come in she said I think you want to go to 
b
ed. She didn't like me to mix with him like that you know. I didn't see so much of him when he was worse for drink. So when she thought he was asleep - gone to sleep, she come down she says - I've been in his trousers pocket - she said I've put a two shil
ling piece and I've stuck it under the bed - she said I'll take you and I on Monday night to pictures.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12530893 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 Was he mean with her or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid655614 SF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 No, I don't know what it was. I suppose she thought be less for him to - but he had the till to go at you se
e - it was his shop. She said we'll go to the pictures on the Monday. Monday afternoon I said are we going tonight. Are we heck she said - when I pulled it out it was a penny. So - oh -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12530893 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 Did you like the job there though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid655614 SF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 Oh we'd plenty of life there you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12530893 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 You liked it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid655614 SF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 Yes, I ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12530893 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 Did you stay there until you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10514531 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid655614 SF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 Yes. And then my sister wouldn't come to the wedding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12530893 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid655614 SF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 Well, she had a - bits of does - in the end she died a terrible death - mental. Had to
 go six months a private patient - he'd pay anything for it. I went to see her once. She said oh Alice will you take your garters off, they've taken me garters off me in here. Oh, she was shocking. She went down in the cellar and the boiler that we used t
o boil the clothes in she filled it with coal. Shocking. Mustn't give them children anything to eat or drink - there's a famine. No lights. She wouldn't have that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12530893 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 Did you work after you were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10514531 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid655614 SF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 No, but I used to go and relieve him a bit while she was ill. Take the child with me you see -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12530893 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 Would you have preferred another kind of job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid655614 SF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 
No, I was happy enough there, you'd plenty of visitors - you'd plenty of people to talk to - we'd crowds there. He could have made a young fortune i
n that place. And then when he come to come out of the place she'd died. I had to give him money to get - lace curtains - there was no curtains up to this house - they'd taken. And he come out with about four thousand out of that shop where his lads - his
 sons were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12530893 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 Do you think that working changed your attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid655614 SF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 Yes, I do. I liked - I liked that job - very, very much. Plenty going on and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12530893 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 Were you in a trade union or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid655614 SF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 Oh no. And a man used to co
me every dinner time - he was the boss over the Broughton copper works - and he used to come at dinner time and be all the nice apples we used to have polished up at the front. I used to give him them you see. Pound of apples, Alice. And then while I'm gi
v
ing him the apples he used to go and get me some sweets from over there. I never though his hands was very clean. 'Course his hands didn't touch the sweets but when he give them me I was frightened in case he'd perhaps - you know - yes, I used to throw th
em away. Well, many a time we used to sell them to somebody else - I'd never eat them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12530893 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 Did you go to church or chapel on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid655614 SF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 I went to Irwell Street. All the way from Broughton to Sal - Irwell Street. Sunday afternoon with my young - my boyf
riend - him and I. And then again at night if it was fine - if not, we used to have a nice little walk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12530893 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 This is what you used to do - go to chapel on Sunday and walk most of the week - go out for walks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid655614 SF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 Yes. Only Monday and Wednesday because when you been in that shop all them hours you don't - really -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12530893 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 Before you met your boyfriend did you have other friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid655614 SF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 Oh yes. I had two young men - two young men - boyfriends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12530893 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 Three boyfriends - you never had girl friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid655614 SF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 No. I - you
 know what I used to do? I used to have one - this one - he was a postman then you see. Well, I had him and then he used to always bring me a nice rose at Saturday night ready for Sunday. And the other one - he used to come and help us in the shop and he 
used to go out with him another night but I used to go out with my boyfriend with the other boyfriends nosegay in me coat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12530893 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 You weren't very true to your boyfriends were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid655614 SF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 No, no. No. I used to think it was laughable. And this one that didn't b
uy me the nosegay - the other one - he used to come and help us on the Saturday night in our shop. Then the other fellow'd come up with the rose - nosegay. I was ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12530893 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 Were you homesick when you were with the vicar?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid655614 SF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 Well, I - after me mother died 
I never seemed to find - have a good life, not when me mother went - I don't know why it was. When you live with sister anybody you know, they get }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10514531 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066  - not the same at all. I missed my mother terrible when she died.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12530893 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 But did you get on all right with the sister whose shop you worked in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid655614 SF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 
Well, you couldn't be very - very friendly - she wouldn't let you be friendly when she was mental. No, you'd a lot to put - I had a - now after I got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10514531 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066  I used to come down from Higher Broughton to Lower
 Broughton for me greengrocery you see. She'd be in that shop, that sister, home made pot of lemon cheese, a bag of oranges and a bag of apples, she used to give 'em to one of them, she wouldn't speak to me. Used to - she used to give 'em then she'd walk 
in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12530893 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 Give them to who?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid655614 SF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 The other assistants - to give to me you see. No, wouldn't speak to me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12530893 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 What age were you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10514531 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 ?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid655614 SF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 Twenty-six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12530893 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 How long had you known your husband then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid655614 SF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 Oh about four years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12530893 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 And where did you meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid655614 SF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 
Well, he used to come to the shop for me but I - I says to him - oh don't come to the shop, she doesn't want you to come in, my sister. You couldn't have any friends - you couldn't with anyone like 'cos ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12530893 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9516112\charrsid12273066 Did you ever bring friends home?
